    "highlight how temperature influences the relative proportions of these phases, suggesting a complex interaction between the thermal conditions and the phase composition of the materials.",
    "Results and DiscussionsAn important feature of this choice of temperatures is our observation that, in the 70: 30 (mol%)Bi 2 O 3 -F e 2 O 3precursor mixture, a liquid phase emerges at 835 • C. This behavior is documented in the phase diagram that we constructed in Figure 1, which integrates and compares several previous works [18][19][20][21][22][23][24], further refined by our own experimental observation marked (g) in red.",
    "This melting is different from the well-known peritectic decomposition of BiF eO 3 at 920 • C (β → γ transition) observed closer to the stoichiometric composition of 1: 1.",
    "Identification of this onset of the liquid phase provides a direct rationale for the deliberate restriction of our sintering temperature to 800 • C in Section 2, ensuring that our study remained focused on the solid-state formation of BiF eO 3 while minimizing melt-assisted secondary phase formation.The phase-pure BiF eO 3 exhibits a rhombohedrally distorted perovskite structure [37] under ambient conditions, which is categorized within the R3c space group (α-BiF eO 3 phase).",
    "In rhombohedral coordinates, its unit cell parameters are defined by a rh = 3.965 Å and α rh = 89."
